d on the persisted conversation-history cooldown before doing the lightweight read. v0.0.131 disables that wait for non-history enumeration. - **Bug 1 is still uncertain.** If the project-specific backend endpoint works after removing `cursor=0`, tasks beyond 20 should become visible. If ChatGPT uses a different endpoint or response shape, the count may remain 20, but v0.0.131 should at least be faster and provide better diagnostic output. - The old global history path remains available behind `--deep-history`, but it is intentionally no longer the default because it caused 429 pressure and added zero tasks in your logs. Run: ```bash pbv pb task list --json \\ 2>&1 | tee pb_task_list_json.v0.0.131.log pb task use 4 --json \\ 2>&1 | tee pb_task_use_4.v0.0.131.log ``` Only if `task list` still shows 20 and you want the slow diagnostic path: ```bash pb task list --deep-history --json \\ 2>&1 | tee pb_task_list_deep_history.v0.0.131.log ``` Verdict: ✅ Strengths — v0.0.131 removes the two obvious self-inflicted delays: persisted history cooldown during lightweight task use, and global history probing during normal task list. ⚠️ Weaknesses — task count >20 still depends on a live backend endpoint whose first v0.0.130 probe failed. 🔍 Unknowns — whether the corrected project endpoint returns all project tasks, or whether another ChatGPT backend route is needed. 🧩 Next step — test v0.0.131 and inspect `source_counts.project_endpoint` plus elapsed time for `pb task use 4`.",
