      "text": "Critical assessment: - **Bug 2 is fixed in v0.0.132.** `pb task use 4 --json` returned directly from the task-list cache with `\"selected_from_task_list_cache\": true`, without the previous service round-trip delay. fileciteturn16file1 - **Bug 1 is still open in v0.0.132.** Normal task listing still returns exactly `count=20`, with `source_counts.snorlax=20`, `project_endpoint=0`, and `dom=0`. fileciteturn15file2 - **Deep history is still not useful for this bug.** It took about 2m40s and still returned only `count=20`; `history=0`, `history_detail=0`, and `project_endpoint=0`. fileciteturn16file2 fileciteturn15file4 Created the next incremental release from `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.132.zip`: [Download `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.133.zip`](sandbox:/mnt/data/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.133.zip) What changed: - Fixed the likely `snorlax/sidebar` pagination bug: - previous logic used the **root cursor** - v0.0.133 prefers the nested `conversations.cursor` for the matched project - reason: the root cursor likely paginates projects/gizmos, while the nested cursor should paginate conversations/tasks inside the selected project - Preserved the v0.0.132 task-list cache behavior. - Added `project_endpoint_diagnostics` into `pb task list --json`. - If `project_endpoint` remains `0`, the CLI JSON should now expose status/body/payload-shape diagnostics instead of forcing us to rely only on container logs. Validation performed: - Python compile check passed for changed core files. - ZIP integrity check passed with `unzip -t`. - ZIP opens directly to repo contents, no wrapper folder. - `VERSION` inside ZIP is `v0.0.133`. - No `__pycache__` or `.pyc` files included. - Focused pytest timed out in this container, so I am **not** claiming pytest passed. Run this next: ```bash pbv pb task list --json \\ 2>&1 | tee pb_task_list_json.v0.0.133.log pb task use 4 --json \\ 2>&1 | tee pb_task_use_4.v0.0.133.log pb task list --deep-history --json \\ 2>&1 | tee pb_task_list_deep_history.v0.0.133.log docker logs --since 30m 0a550f42843e \\ > promptbranch-service:0.0.133.log ``` Important: capture Docker logs **after** the `pb` commands. The v0.0.132 docker log command was run before the test commands, so it could not contain the useful run data. Expected signals: ```json \"selected_from_task_list_cache\": true ``` for `pb task use 4`. For bug 1, the main signal is: ```json \"source_counts\": { \"snorlax\": 21 } ``` or higher. If `snorlax` remains `20`, inspect the new: ```json \"project_endpoint_diagnostics\": [...] ``` Confidence level: - **High** that `task use 4` remains fixed. - **Medium** that v0.0.133 fixes tasks beyond 20, because it targets the most likely cursor bug, but live backend behavior still has to confirm it. Verdict: ✅ Strengths — confirmed cache fix retained; likely cursor misuse addressed; better diagnostics added to CLI JSON. ⚠️ Weaknesses — task count >20 still depends on live backend/snorlax cursor behavior. 🔍 Unknowns — whether the matched project row actually exposes a usable nested `conversations.cursor` in your live session. 🧩 Next step — run v0.0.133 and check whether `source_counts.snorlax` rises above 20.",
