      "text": "It depends on **which MCP host** you use. Most likely locations: ### Cursor Project-local config: ```bash mkdir -p .cursor nano .cursor/mcp.json ``` Put the block in: ```json { \"mcpServers\": { \"promptbranch\": { \"command\": \"/home/spikkie/.local/share/pipx/venvs/promptbranch/bin/promptbranch\", \"args\": [ \"--profile-dir\", \"/home/spikkie/git/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow/.pb_profile\", \"mcp\", \"serve\", \"--path\", \"/home/spikkie/git/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow\" ] } } } ``` Cursor also supports MCP configuration through its MCP settings/docs; project-level `.cursor/mcp.json` is commonly used. citeturn888964search5turn888964search12 ### Claude Desktop Use Claude Desktop’s config JSON, usually named: ```text claude_desktop_config.json ``` Add the `mcpServers` block there, then restart Claude Desktop. The official MCP docs use Claude Desktop as the local-server example and describe adding local MCP servers through config. citeturn888964search0 ### VS Code / other MCP host Use that host’s MCP config/settings file and add the same `mcpServers.promptbranch` entry. The key is that the host must launch this command: ```bash /home/spikkie/.local/share/pipx/venvs/promptbranch/bin/promptbranch --profile-dir /home/spikkie/git/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow/.pb_profile mcp serve --path /home/spikkie/git/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow ``` Critical point: **do not paste it into Promptbranch config**. Paste it into the config of the program that will consume MCP tools: Cursor, Claude Desktop, VS Code, etc. Verdict: ✅ Strengths — your generated config is valid and uses absolute paths. ⚠️ Weaknesses — exact file location depends on the MCP host. 🔍 Unknowns — you have not said which host you are using. 🧩 Next step — tell me the host name: Cursor, Claude Desktop, VS Code, Claude Code, or something else.",
      "create_time": 1777733583.763183
    },
    {
      "index": 827,
      "id": "abfabb4f-8f11-4bfe-9ac7-45456b7cc9b9",
      "role": "user",
      "text": "On my local machine on which I run promptbranch, we also have to create a mCP client and MCP host. I have already a ± |main U:1 ✗| → ollama --help Large language model runner Usage: ollama [flags] ollama [command] and a graphical cpu with 6Gb of mem how to continue?",
      "create_time": 1777734108.065
