      "id": "ec71d562-fe65-4bcb-8e29-5cfaeac89b3d",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "What happened: Your Ollama setup works, but **`qwen2.5-coder:3b` failed the only test we cared about**: strict JSON output. You asked: ```text Return only JSON. Classify this request... ``` It returned repeated Python-average nonsense. That means: ```text Ollama installed ✅ Models downloaded ✅ qwen2.5-coder:3b usable as trusted JSON classifier ❌ ``` So your confusion is justified. The model ignored the instruction and hallucinated unrelated code. ### Why this matters For the Promptbranch agent, we need the local model to produce something like: ```json {\"intent\":\"inspect_repo\",\"risk\":\"read\",\"tools\":[\"filesystem.read\",\"git.status\"]} ``` Instead it produced prose/code spam. If we let that drive MCP tool calls, it becomes unreliable. ### What to do next Test with Ollama’s structured-output API instead of plain `ollama run`. Ollama supports JSON mode / schema-based structured output via the API `format` field. citeturn536929search0turn536929search5 Run this: ```bash curl -s http://localhost:11434/api/generate \\ -d '{ \"model\": \"qwen2.5-coder:3b\", \"prompt\": \"Classify this request: read VERSION and git status. Return JSON only.\", \"stream\": false, \"format\": { \"type\": \"object\", \"properties\": { \"intent\": {\"type\": \"string\"}, \"risk\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"read\", \"write\"]}, \"tools\": { \"type\": \"array\", \"items\": {\"type\": \"string\"} } }, \"required\": [\"intent\", \"risk\", \"tools\"] }, \"options\": { \"temperature\": 0 } }' | jq . ``` Expected shape: ```json { \"model\": \"qwen2.5-coder:3b\", \"response\": \"{\\\"intent\\\":\\\"inspect_repo\\\",\\\"risk\\\":\\\"read\\\",\\\"tools\\\":[\\\"filesystem.read\\\",\\\"git.status\\\"]}\", ... } ``` Then parse just the response: ```bash curl -s http://localhost:11434/api/generate \\ -d '{ \"model\": \"qwen2.5-coder:3b\", \"prompt\": \"Classify this request: read VERSION and git status. Return JSON only.\", \"stream\": false, \"format\": { \"type\": \"object\", \"properties\": { \"intent\": {\"type\": \"string\"}, \"risk\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"read\", \"write\"]}, \"tools\": { \"type\": \"array\", \"items\": {\"type\": \"string\"} } }, \"required\": [\"intent\", \"risk\", \"tools\"] }, \"options\": { \"temperature\": 0 } }' | jq -r .response | jq . ``` Also test `llama3.2:3b`: ```bash curl -s http://localhost:11434/api/generate \\ -d '{ \"model\": \"llama3.2:3b\", \"prompt\": \"Classify this request: read VERSION and git status. Return JSON only.\", \"stream\": false, \"format\": { \"type\": \"object\", \"properties\": { \"intent\": {\"type\": \"string\"}, \"risk\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"read\", \"write\"]}, \"tools\": { \"type\": \"array\", \"items\": {\"type\": \"string\"} } }, \"required\": [\"intent\", \"risk\", \"tools\"] }, \"options\": { \"temperature\": 0 } }' | jq -r .response | jq . ``` ### The architecture remains the same Do **not** let Ollama execute anything. Use it like this: ```text User request ↓ Ollama proposes intent JSON ↓ Promptbranch validates intent deterministically ↓ Promptbranch MCP client calls read-only tools ↓ Ollama summarizes tool results ``` For now, if structured output still fails, the correct fallback is: ```text Rule-based classifier for tool choice Ollama only for summarizing results ``` Confidence: high. Verdict: ✅ Strengths — Ollama and the models are installed correctly. ⚠️ Weaknesses — plain `ollama run` is not reliable enough for strict JSON planning. 🔍 Unknowns — whether `qwen2.5-coder:3b` behaves correctly under schema-constrained API mode. 🧩 Next step — run the `curl ... format schema ...` test above for both `qwen2.5-coder:3b` and `llama3.2:3b`.",
