      "text": "Yes. Make it simpler. The hang is probably because `stream=false` waits until the model finishes. If the model starts rambling again, `curl -s` looks frozen. ### 1. First check Ollama is alive ```bash id=\"x0uqji\" curl -s http://localhost:11434/api/tags | jq . ``` ### 2. Use a short timeout and small output ```bash id=\"16gbn1\" timeout 20s curl -s http://localhost:11434/api/generate \\ -d '{ \"model\": \"llama3.2:3b\", \"prompt\": \"Return JSON only: {\\\"intent\\\":\\\"inspect_repo\\\",\\\"risk\\\":\\\"read\\\",\\\"tools\\\":[\\\"filesystem.read\\\",\\\"git.status\\\"]}\", \"stream\": false, \"format\": \"json\", \"options\": { \"temperature\": 0, \"num_predict\": 80 } }' | jq -r .response | jq . ``` Try `llama3.2:3b` first, not `qwen2.5-coder:3b`. ### 3. If that still hangs, stream it ```bash id=\"tb5x8g\" curl -N http://localhost:11434/api/generate \\ -d '{ \"model\": \"llama3.2:3b\", \"prompt\": \"Return JSON only: {\\\"intent\\\":\\\"inspect_repo\\\",\\\"risk\\\":\\\"read\\\",\\\"tools\\\":[\\\"filesystem.read\\\",\\\"git.status\\\"]}\", \"stream\": true, \"format\": \"json\", \"options\": { \"temperature\": 0, \"num_predict\": 80 } }' ``` ### 4. Practical decision If this does not return clean JSON quickly, do **not** use Ollama for tool planning yet. Use this safer design: ```text id=\"cbp1rb\" Promptbranch rule-based planner chooses tools Ollama only summarizes tool results ``` So for now: ```text id=\"9p85e4\" \"read VERSION and git status\" → deterministic planner → filesystem.read VERSION → git.status → optional Ollama summary ``` Verdict: ✅ Strengths — Ollama is installed and models exist. ⚠️ Weaknesses — current local model behavior is unreliable for strict planning. 🔍 Unknowns — whether `llama3.2:3b` behaves better with `format:\"json\"` and `num_predict`. 🧩 Next step — run the shorter `llama3.2:3b` command above; if it fails, skip LLM planning and make v0.0.142 rule-based with Ollama summary only.",
