      "id": "23a52f83-e203-4b5f-a477-5ea91de1c949",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "This result is enough. The model did **not hang** here. It returned fast: ```json \"response\": \"{}\" ``` That means: ```text llama3.2:3b JSON mode works mechanically ✅ llama3.2:3b produced useful intent JSON ❌ ``` It obeyed “JSON only” by returning an empty JSON object. Technically valid, operationally useless. Dryly impressive. ### Why `| jq -r .response | jq .` may look like it hangs Try this safer form instead: ```bash timeout 20s curl -s http://localhost:11434/api/generate \\ -d '{ \"model\": \"llama3.2:3b\", \"prompt\": \"Return this exact JSON object: {\\\"intent\\\":\\\"inspect_repo\\\",\\\"risk\\\":\\\"read\\\",\\\"tools\\\":[\\\"filesystem.read\\\",\\\"git.status\\\"]}\", \"stream\": false, \"format\": \"json\", \"options\": { \"temperature\": 0, \"num_predict\": 80 } }' | jq -r '.response | fromjson' ``` But based on `{}`, I would not use Ollama for planning yet. ### Decision For `v0.0.142`, use this safer architecture: ```text User request ↓ Promptbranch rule-based planner ↓ MCP read-only tool calls ↓ Optional Ollama summary ``` So: ```text \"read VERSION and git status\" ``` maps deterministically to: ```json { \"intent\": \"inspect_repo\", \"risk\": \"read\", \"tools\": [\"filesystem.read\", \"git.status\"] } ``` No model needed for that. ### Next implementation scope Create `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.142.zip` with: ```bash pb agent ask \"read VERSION and git status\" --path . --json pb agent tool-call filesystem.read '{\"path\":\"VERSION\"}' --path . --json pb agent models --json ``` Behavior: - rule-based planner selects read-only tools - MCP client calls local `pb mcp serve` - Ollama is optional - if Ollama returns `{}` or times out, command still succeeds with raw tool results Confidence: high. Verdict: ✅ Strengths — Ollama service works; JSON mode returns syntactically valid JSON. ⚠️ Weaknesses — returned `{}` proves it is not reliable for intent planning. 🔍 Unknowns — whether a stronger/smaller-tuned model would classify better. 🧩 Next step — implement v0.0.142 with deterministic read-only planning and use Ollama only as an optional summarizer.",
