      "id": "671e79e6-424e-4a5a-878d-624be981fe74",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "The Ollama test confirms the weak point: - `ollama` is running. - `llama3.2:3b` can return JSON-mode output. - But it returned invalid/repetitive garbage for a simple exact-JSON instruction. - Therefore Ollama is **not reliable enough for tool planning** yet. So I created the next release with the safer architecture: deterministic read-only planning, MCP tool execution, and Ollama optional only for summaries. [Download `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.142.zip`](sandbox:/mnt/data/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.142.zip) What changed: ```bash pb agent ask \"read VERSION and git status\" --path . --json pb agent tool-call filesystem.read '{\"path\":\"VERSION\"}' --path . --json pb agent models --json ``` Behavior: - `pb agent ask` uses a **rule-based read-only planner**. - It maps `\"read VERSION and git status\"` to: - `filesystem.read VERSION` - `git.status` - Ollama is **not used for planning**. - Ollama can be used only for optional summaries via `--model` or `--summarize`. - If Ollama returns `{}`, invalid JSON, or times out, the command still succeeds with raw tool results. - Write-capable tools remain blocked. Validation performed: - `py_compile` passed for changed files. - Focused MCP tests passed: `16 passed`. - CLI parser tests passed: `30 passed`. - Manual CLI checks passed for: - `pb agent ask \"read VERSION and git status\" --path . --json` - `pb agent tool-call filesystem.read '{\"path\":\"VERSION\"}' --path . --json` - blocking `promptbranch.src.sync` through `agent tool-call` - ZIP integrity check passed. - ZIP opens directly to repo contents, no wrapper folder. - `VERSION` is `v0.0.142`. - No `__pycache__`, `.pyc`, or `.pytest_cache` entries included. Run next: ```bash pbv pb agent ask \"read VERSION and git status\" --path . --json \\ 2>&1 | tee pb_agent_ask_readonly.v0.0.142.log pb agent tool-call filesystem.read '{\"path\":\"VERSION\"}' --path . --json \\ 2>&1 | tee pb_agent_tool_call_version.v0.0.142.log pb agent models --json \\ 2>&1 | tee pb_agent_models.v0.0.142.log ``` Confidence: high for deterministic read-only agent behavior; low for Ollama summaries until your local model behaves better. Verdict: ✅ Strengths — avoids trusting unreliable local model output; executes only deterministic read-only MCP tools. ⚠️ Weaknesses — no autonomous tool planning; no write execution. 🔍 Unknowns — whether a different local model can summarize cleanly enough to be useful. 🧩 Next step — test v0.0.142 with the three commands above, then decide whether Ollama should remain summary-only or be dropped entirely from the first local-agent loop.",
