      "id": "bb0bae20-b49f-4e0f-8d5f-fbb270d611b7",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "In the current code, **two things can call the MCP server**: ## 1. External MCP host/client When you run: ```bash pb mcp serve --path . ``` Promptbranch starts an MCP server over stdio. Then an external MCP host/client can call it, for example: ```text Cursor / Claude Desktop / another MCP host → starts pb mcp serve → sends JSON-RPC over stdin → receives JSON-RPC over stdout ``` That is the “real MCP” path. Example raw client: ```bash printf '%s\\n' \\ '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"initialize\",\"params\":{}}' \\ '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":2,\"method\":\"tools/call\",\"params\":{\"name\":\"filesystem.read\",\"arguments\":{\"path\":\"VERSION\"}}}' \\ | pb mcp serve --path . ``` Here, **your shell pipeline is acting as the MCP client**. ## 2. `pb agent ...` commands In v0.0.142, `pb agent ask` and `pb agent tool-call` use the **same MCP tool implementation layer**, but they do **not necessarily spawn `pb mcp serve` as a separate stdio process**. Conceptually: ```text pb agent ask → rule-based planner → internal MCP tool dispatcher → filesystem.read / git.status ``` So for your command: ```bash pb agent ask \"read VERSION and git status\" --path . --json ``` the caller is: ```text promptbranch CLI itself ``` It calls the MCP tool functions internally. It is **not Ollama** and **not ChatGPT**. Your own output confirms that: ```json \"ollama\": { \"used_for_planning\": false, \"used_for_summary\": false, \"model\": null } ``` ## Clear separation ```text pb mcp serve = MCP server mode = waits for JSON-RPC requests from an external client/host pb agent ask = Promptbranch-local agent mode = uses rule-based planning and calls the same read-only tools directly/internal path Ollama = currently not calling MCP = currently not selecting tools ``` ## Current call chain for your successful test ```text You ↓ pb agent ask \"read VERSION and git status\" ↓ Promptbranch CLI ↓ rule_based_v1 planner ↓ filesystem.read VERSION git.status ↓ JSON output ``` Not: ```text You → Ollama → MCP server → tools ``` and not: ```text You → ChatGPT → MCP server → tools ``` Verdict: ✅ Strengths — the current path is deterministic and does not trust the broken Ollama JSON output. ⚠️ Weaknesses — `pb agent ask` is not yet a true external MCP client/host loop. 🔍 Unknowns — whether you want the next step to force `pb agent` to call `pb mcp serve` via stdio for stricter end-to-end MCP realism. 🧩 Next step — add an explicit `pb agent ask --transport stdio` mode if you want the agent to exercise the actual MCP server boundary instead of the internal dispatcher.",
