      "text": "Implemented the first **Ollama → validated MCP stdio** test path. [Download `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.143.zip`](sandbox:/mnt/data/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.143.zip) What changed: ```bash pb agent mcp-llm-smoke \"read VERSION\" --path . --model llama3.2:3b --json ``` This does the test you asked for: ```text Ollama model ↓ proposes one MCP tool call as JSON Promptbranch ↓ validates tool is read-only and allowed Promptbranch MCP client ↓ calls actual pb mcp serve over stdio MCP server ↓ executes filesystem.read / git.status / etc. JSON result ``` Important safety boundary: - Ollama does **not** execute anything. - Ollama only proposes: ```json {\"tool\":\"filesystem.read\",\"arguments\":{\"path\":\"VERSION\",\"max_bytes\":2000}} ``` - Promptbranch rejects: - invalid JSON - missing tool name - unknown tools - write tools - destructive tools - Only validated read-only tools reach the MCP server. Validation performed: - `tests/test_promptbranch_mcp.py`: `20 passed` - `tests/test_cli_parser.py`: `30 passed` - `tests/test_promptbranch_cli.py`: included in focused run - combined focused CLI/MCP suite: `94 passed` - container API version tests: `12 passed` - ZIP integrity check passed. - ZIP opens directly to repo contents, no wrapper folder. - `VERSION` is `v0.0.143`. - No `__pycache__`, `.pyc`, or `.pytest_cache` entries included. Run next: ```bash pbv pb agent mcp-llm-smoke \"read VERSION\" --path . --model llama3.2:3b --json \\ 2>&1 | tee pb_agent_mcp_llm_smoke.v0.0.143.log ``` Expected good path: ```json { \"ok\": true, \"status\": \"verified\", \"mode\": \"ollama_proposes_validated_mcp_stdio\" } ``` Expected failure path, if Ollama emits garbage again: ```json { \"ok\": false, \"status\": \"model_tool_call_invalid\", \"mcp\": null } ``` That failure would still be useful: it proves the model is not yet good enough to propose MCP calls, while the guardrail prevents bad execution. Verdict: ✅ Strengths — first real model-proposed MCP stdio pa