      "id": "6c307728-34b0-44c3-b321-c95ae0ab390f",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "The first run is a clean negative result, but it also exposes one harness flaw: MCP tool names like `filesystem.read` may be harder for local tool-calling models than simple names like `filesystem_read`. I’ll adjust the test approach to use model-facing aliases and map them back to MCP names.",
