      "index": 955,
      "id": "7da8da4b-33cb-4d67-92b7-ee54c9dbebb7",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "It is probably **not a Python hang**. It is stuck waiting on the **LangChain → Ollama streaming response**. Your traceback shows the blocked point: ```text ChatOllama(...).bind_tools(...).invoke(...) → ollama client chat stream → httpx iter_lines() → socket recv() ``` So the sequence is: ```text verify_ollama_mcp_trust_v2.py → raw Ollama schema test → raw Ollama chat-tools test → LangChain ChatOllama bind_tools test ↳ waits for Ollama stream ``` The problem is in the `--try-langchain` branch. In v2, the LangChain call does **not enforce the harness timeout cleanly** and does **not limit generated tokens enough**. If the model starts rambling, LangChain waits on the stream. ### Immediate workaround Run without LangChain first: ```bash python3 verify_ollama_mcp_trust_v2.py \\ --repo-path /home/spikkie/git/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow \\ --models qwen2.5-coder:3b \\ --execute-first-valid ``` Then test LangChain under a shell timeout: ```bash timeout 45s python3 verify_ollama_mcp_trust_v2.py \\ --repo-path /home/spikkie/git/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow \\ --models qwen2.5-coder:3b \\ --try-langchain \\ --execute-first-valid ``` ### Better practical test Do **not** use `qwen2.5-coder:3b` for the LangChain tool test. It already failed badly in the earlier run. Try one model at a time: ```bash timeout 60s python3 verify_ollama_mcp_trust_v2.py \\ --repo-path /home/spikkie/git/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow \\ --models llama3.1:8b \\ --try-langchain \\ --execute-first-valid ``` or, after pulling it: ```bash ollama pull llama3-groq-tool-use:8b timeout 60s python3 verify_ollama_mcp_trust_v2.py \\ --repo-path /home/spikkie/git/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow \\ --models llama3-groq-tool-use:8b \\ --try-langchain \\ --execute-first-valid ``` ### What to change in the harness The v2 harness needs one fix: wrap the LangChain call in a hard subprocess or signal timeout. Python-level `timeout` arguments are not reliable here because LangChain/Ollama streams can block inside HTTP reads. For now, safest rule: ```text raw Ollama API tests = useful LangChain test = optional, run only under shell timeout ``` ### My current interpretation This is not proof that LangChain is bad. It means: ```text qwen2.5-coder:3b + LangChain bind_tools + no hard timeout = bad test setup ``` The correct conclusion is narrower: ```text Do not use qwen2.5-coder:3b for tool planning. Do not run LangChain tests without a hard timeout. Try better tool-capable 8B models. ``` Confidence: high. Verdict: ✅ Strengths — the traceback clearly identifies the blocking layer. ⚠️ Weaknesses — v2 harness does not hard-timeout the LangChain branch. 🔍 Unknowns — whether a better tool-use model behaves correctly under LangChain. 🧩 Next step — rerun without `--try-langchain`, then test `llama3.1:8b` or `llama3-groq-tool-use:8b` with `timeout 60s`.",
