      "text": "The v0.0.146 logs exposed two failures, one real code bug and one integration-suite classification bug. 1. `pb agent ollama-propose \"read VERSION\"` worked: it classified the original request as read-only, selected `read_file -> filesystem.read`, and validated the proposal. One native Ollama tool-call path timed out, but the schema fallback succeeded. fileciteturn53file13 2. `pb agent mcp-llm-smoke ...` failed before reaching Ollama/MCP because the parser option `--command` overwrote the root parser’s `command` field, leaving `args.command=None`. Both read and delete smoke commands crashed with `RuntimeError: Unknown command: None`. fileciteturn51file1 fileciteturn51file0 3. `pb test-suite --json` still failed at `task_message_flow.task_list_visible`. The created task was matched from `project_endpoint`, but the suite did not count `project_endpoint` as indexed visibility. That contradicts the current backend-first project task enumeration model. fileciteturn53file15 Created the next incremental release from `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.146.zip`: [Download `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.147.zip`](sandbox:/mnt/data/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.147.zip) Changes: - Fixed `pb agent mcp-llm-smoke` parser bug: - `--command` now stores into `mcp_executable` - it no longer overwrites root `args.command` - Fixed integration-suite task visibility: - `project_endpoint` now counts as indexed visibility - `recent_state` remains degraded fallback only - Preserved v0.0.146 Ollama guardrails: - original request risk is classified before model proposal execution - destructive/write prompts must fail closed - model-facing aliases remain mapped to real MCP tools Validation performed: - `py_compile` passed for changed files. - Direct parser assertions passed for: - `pb agent mcp-llm-smoke \"read VERSION\" ...` - `pb agent mcp-llm-smoke \"delete VERSION\" ...` - `pb agent mcp-llm-smoke ... --command /tmp/pb` - `pb agent ollama-propose ...` - Direct visibility assertions passed: - `project_endpoint` = indexed - `recent_state` = not indexed - ZIP integrity check passed. - ZIP opens directly to repo contents, no wrapper folder. - `VERSION` is `v0.0.147`. Full pytest was attempted but timed out in this container, so I am not claiming a full-suite pass. Run next: ```bash pbv pb agent mcp-llm-smoke \"read VERSION\" --path . --model llama3-groq-tool-use:8b --json \\ 2>&1 | tee pb_agent_mcp_llm_smoke_read_version.v0.0.147.log pb agent mcp-llm-smoke \"delete VERSION\" --path . --model llama3-groq-tool-use:8b --json \\ 2>&1 | tee pb_agent_mcp_llm_smoke_delete_version.v0.0.147.log pb test-suite --json \\ 2>&1 | tee pb_test-suite.v0.0.147.log ``` Expected negative-test result: ```json { \"ok\": false, \"status\": \"risk_rejected\", \"mcp\": null } ``` Verdict: ✅ Strengths — fixes the parser crash and aligns task visibility with the project endpoint that now provides reliable indexed task rows. ⚠️ Weaknesses — live Ollama behavior still depends on local model timing; native chat-tools may timeout and fall back to schema mode. 🔍 Unknowns — whether the full live suite now passes under current ChatGPT timing. 🧩 Next step — test v0.0.147 with the three commands above.",
