      "id": "2d877d55-4a2c-4b34-9d3c-fdf49d09329a",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "v0.0.148 looks good. The remaining risk is not the new MCP/skill path; it is future scope creep into write/process execution before the guardrails are ready. Results checked: - `pb agent host-smoke --path . --json` passed with `status=verified`; command resolution is absolute, MCP initialize/tools/state/filesystem/git checks passed, and write tools were not executed. fileciteturn64file9 - `pb agent mcp-call filesystem.read '{\"path\":\"VERSION\"}'` passed via stdio and returned `v0.0.148`. fileciteturn62file0 - `pb agent run \"read VERSION and git status\"` passed via the Promptbranch-native host path; it planned `filesystem.read` and `git.status`, both executed through MCP stdio, and git status was clean on `main` at `5e0426c`. fileciteturn62file1 - `pb skill validate .promptbranch/skills/repo-inspection` passed; no unknown tools and no write tools. fileciteturn64file14 - `pb agent run --skill repo-inspection \"inspect repo\"` passed; it validated the skill, planned `filesystem.read`, `git.status`, and `git.diff.summary`, and executed all three via MCP stdio. fileciteturn62file2 - `pb agent run \"delete VERSION\"` correctly failed closed with `status=risk_rejected`, `risk=destructive`, `matched_terms=[\"delete\"]`, empty plan, and no results. fileciteturn65file15 Critical assessment: - The MVP-A/MVP-B path is now proven locally: Promptbranch host → MCP client → MCP server → read-only tools. - The repo is clean during the tested `git.status`, which removes one packaging ambiguity. - The design still correctly blocks write/destructive execution. That matches the planned non-goals: no autonomous source overwrite, artifact release, broad shell execution, or write-capable MCP yet. fileciteturn65file16 - The missing piece is controlled process execution, not source/artifact writes. Verdict: ✅ Strengths — v0.0.148 validates the native MCP host/client loop and local skill registry. ⚠️ Weaknesses — no controlled test execution yet; no artifact/source mutation should be added yet. 🔍 Unknowns — whether process tools can be constrained cleanly enough without becoming arbitrary shell execution. 🧩 Next step — implement MVP-D narrowly: add `test.smoke` as a controlled process MCP tool with timeout/stdout/stderr/exit-code capture, then wire `pb agent run \"run smoke tests\"` to that tool.",
      "create_time": 1777825601.820318
